article.description: Deang Deang had 21 points as Eastern Illinois easily defeated Chicago State 98-34 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Deang scores 21 to carry E. Illinois past Chicago St. 98-34
article.linkText: Deang scores 21 to carry E. Illinois past Chicago St. 98-34
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Deang Deang had 21 points as Eastern Illinois easily defeated Chicago State 98-34 on Tuesday night. George Dixon had 15 points and nine rebounds for Eastern Illinois (1-2). Marvin Johnson added 14 points and seven rebounds. Mack Smith had 13 points for the hosts. Andrew Lewis had 14 points for the Cougars (1-2). Jace Colley added three blocks. Xavier Johnson, the Cougars' leading scorer heading into the matchup at 28.0 points per game, was held to 4 points on 2-of-12 shooting. Eastern Illinois plays Indiana-Northwest at home on Monday. Chicago State matches up against Purdue on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
